TY  - JOUR
T1  - General System(s) Theory: The Promise That Could Not Be Kept
AU  - Thayer, Frederick
Y1  - 1972/12/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255143
DO  - 10.5465/255143
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 481
EP  - 493
VL  - 15
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - General System(s) Theory (GST) has failed to deliver because of its own basic assumptions. Hierarchy compels us to impersonalize all social interaction, thus making it impossible to realize ourselves. Concreteness overemphasizes the single organization and determinism as well. Competition returns us to the mechanistic tradition GST initially sought to escape. Finally, GST remains tied to ?laws? of growth which promise only our destruction. American Indians knew better.
