TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Control Structure of Organizations: an Empirical Examination: Reply
AU  - McMahon, J. Timothy
AU  - Perritt, G. W.
Y1  - 1972/12/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255149
DO  - 10.5465/255149
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 544
EP  - 546
VL  - 15
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a reply to comments made by Arnold Tannenbaum on the authors' review of Tannenbaum's book ?Control in Organizations.? In his comments, Tannenbaum claimed that the authors' criticisms were unfounded on the basis that each criticism could not be factually supported. The authors, using passages from Tannenbaum's book, assert that the methodologies employed did not take into account the differences of opinion between ranks in organizations regarding control systems. Also, it is mentioned that the authors were not in agreement with the book as stated by Tannenbaum, and several reasons are given for a study performed by the authors, which Tannenbaum criticized.
AB  - The article presents a reply to comments made by Arnold Tannenbaum on the authors' review of Tannenbaum's book ?Control in Organizations.? In his comments, Tannenbaum claimed that the authors' criticisms were unfounded on the basis that each criticism could not be factually supported. The authors, using passages from Tannenbaum's book, assert that the methodologies employed did not take into account the differences of opinion between ranks in organizations regarding control systems. Also, it is mentioned that the authors were not in agreement with the book as stated by Tannenbaum, and several reasons are given for a study performed by the authors, which Tannenbaum criticized.
